# Environment Variables & Secrets

- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or URLs — always use environment variables
- Client-safe vars must be prefixed with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` — all others are server-only
- Server-only vars must never be imported in client components (`"use client"` files)
- Always add new vars to `.env.example` with a placeholder value

```bash
# .env.example
DATABASE_URL=your_postgresql_connection_string
NEXTAUTH_URL=https://yourdomain.com
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your_secret_min_32_chars
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://yourdomain.com
```

- `.env` is gitignored — never commit real secrets
- Use `process.env.VAR_NAME` directly — no abstraction layers around env vars unless there's a real need
